{"lemma":"زَمْزَمُ","slug":"زَمْزَمُ","root":"ز.م.ز.م","root_slug":"ز-م-ز-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-م-ز-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18069","n18070","n18071"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"abundant water"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Zamzam"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chant, to intone","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make consecutive sound"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thunder","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to produce a crackling sound, to be crepitant","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gather, to collect","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wash with Zamzam water"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/zam.zam/","/zam.za.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18069","headword_ar":"زَمْزَمٌ","root":"zm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Copious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"water; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumaAzimN","text_ar":"زُمَازِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [or] the latter, (Kz, TA,) [and app. the former also,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumazimN","text_ar":"زُمَزِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKh, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozaAmN","text_ar":"زَمْزَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kz, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brackish"},{"kind":"text","text":"water; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is between salt and sweet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKh, Kz, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (accord. to some copies of the S and K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozamu","text_ar":"زَمْزَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to other copies of the same, and accord. to the Msb,) imperfectly decl., because of the fem. gender and a proper name, (Msb,) the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The well of Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in a copy of the S and in the Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"celebrated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well in Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in another copy of the S,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain well adjacent to the Kaabeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) so called [because its water is somewhat brackish, or] because of the copiousness of its water; (JM;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumazim","text_ar":"زُمَزِم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumazimN","text_ar":"زُمَزِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumazimu","text_ar":"زُمَزِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (IAar, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumaAzimN","text_ar":"زُمَازِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumaAzimu","text_ar":"زُمَازِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zam~amN","text_ar":"زَمَّمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zam~amu","text_ar":"زَمَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K,) the last ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zam~am","text_ar":"زَمَّم"},{"kind":"text","text":") on the authority of IAar. (TA.) The names of this well, collected from trads. and lexicons, have been found to amount to more than sixty. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozam","text_ar":"زَمْزَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with or without tenween] is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A celebrated well at El-Medeeneh, which is regarded as a means of obtaining a blessing, and the water of which is drunk and transported"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like that of the more celebrated well of the same name at Mekkeh]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozamN","text_ar":"زَمْزَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozamu","text_ar":"زَمْزَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to different copies of the S, [used by a poet with tenween, but probably by poetic license, for it is app. a fem. proper name, and therefore imperfectly decl.,]) is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, a she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayoTal","text_ar":"عَيْطَل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Kz","TA","IKh","Msb","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n18070","headword_ar":"زِمْزِمٌ","root":"zm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zimozimapN","text_ar":"زِمْزِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18071","headword_ar":"زُمَزِمٌ","root":"zm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zumazimu","text_ar":"زُمَزِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamozamN","text_ar":"زَمْزَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}